main event: A radar object was tracked at Kadena Air Base, Okinawa on April 25, 1960.
interesting points: The object was tracked on radar moving at very high speed, disappearing at 045Â° azimuth.
The object was tracked for about 10 minutes while the base was also tracking an aircraft at 26,000 feet.
The object was observed at a range of 55-65,000 feet, maintaining an even course and speed.
No unusual weather or astronomical conditions were reported that could account for the sighting.
The object could not be identified and was suspected to be a man-made satellite or of unknown origin.
